	CPMs request    
	The CPM wants the government to seriously consider a matter. No, its got nothing to do with the nuclear deal, but with the possible name for the new airport in Bangalore. The CPM wants to name the airport after Tipu Sultan.     
	In a letter to Prime Minister Manmohan Singh, party leader Sitaram Yechury said the new airport was coming up in Devanahalli, which happens to be the birthplace of Tipu Sultan. May I request you to seriously consider naming this airport after Tipu Sultan. This would be a befitting gesture to a person who valiantly fought the British in the 18th century, Yechury said and expressed hope for a favourable response from the government.     
